abstract = {It is hypothesized that terrestrial plants are the product of an ancient and continuing symbiosis of a semi-aquatic ancestral green alga and an aquatic fungus \textemdash an oomycete. The Siluro-Devonian \textquotedblleftexplosive\textquotedblright colonization of land, and indeed the very evolution of plants, was possible only through such mutualistic partnerships \textemdash partnerships that were equipped to cope with the problems of desiccation and starvation associated with terrestrial existence.}
